The paper deals with the generation and detection of manipulated videos with realistic synthetic faces, which falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new dataset for face manipulation, which involves the use of machine learning techniques such as generative refinement models (cs.MM) and benchmarks for image forensic tasks such as classification and segmentation (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the challenges of distinguishing between original and manipulated videos, which requires the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning algorithms (cs.LG).
